{
  "text": "Gel-free proteomic approaches may be additionally divided as \"bottom-up\" and \"top-down\". The first refers to the identification of proteins by analysis of peptides obtained by specific proteolysis. Peptide masses and sequences obtained using tandem mass spectrometry are used to identify corresponding proteins. The \"top-down\" proteomics uses masses of intact proteins and their fragments for identification and characterization [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The top-down proteomic approach, using MALDI-based tandem mass spectrometry might be used in the identification of bacterial protein biomarkers and toxins even from unfractionated bacterial cell lysates [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
